<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[264,1323,284,1030]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,453,884,910]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Discussion:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[460,713,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Mycolybas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipennis">
<emphasis box="[460,713,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Mycolybas rufipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibits characters otherwise atypical of 
<taxonomicName box="[1196,1323,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Mycolybas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1196,1323,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Mycolybas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(absence of coxal lines, truncate base of scutellum and tibiae moderately expanded distally). However, 
<taxonomicName box="[526,700,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Mycolybas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipennis">
<emphasis box="[526,700,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. rufipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains in 
<taxonomicName box="[883,1010,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Mycolybas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[883,1010,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Mycolybas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until a comprehensive phylogenetic analysis is completed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
